+{"id":"franken_networkx-k4mg","title":"parity: attachment generators should accept backend keyword surface","description":"barabasi_albert_graph and powerlaw_cluster_graph are missing NetworkX's backend-dispatch keyword surface. FrankenNetworkX currently rejects backend/backend_kwargs with unexpected-keyword TypeError, while upstream NetworkX accepts the keywords and then raises ImportError when the requested backend is unavailable. Match the public backend keyword contract for these attachment-style generators.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T13:02:30.433374380Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T13:02:30.433374380Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-p2rq","title":"parity: tree and shell random generators should expose NetworkX keyword surface","description":"random_lobster, random_shell_graph, and random_powerlaw_tree do not expose the full NetworkX public keyword surface. random_lobster currently rejects create_using entirely, and all three generators are missing backend/backend_kwargs. Upstream NetworkX accepts those keywords and either constructs into the requested graph class or raises ImportError for an unavailable backend. Match the public keyword contract for these tree/shell random generators.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T13:02:30.433374380Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T13:02:30.433374380Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
